, IGDS1","Notizie degli scavi di antichità, 1876-","Hoffmann, 1904, SGDI","Roehl, 1907","Jeffery, Johnston, 1990, The local scripts of archaic Greece","Jeffery, 1961, The Local Scripts of Archaic Greece",[273,274,275,276,277,278],"RWXNUFEX","4MCP2PVV","DQDPC573","KV7SJ9VF","QUWGZA84","V6CGSWPS",[280,281,282,20,25,29,283,283,284,285,286,287,288,152],"isic001484","epitaph of philistidas, son of euxenos",{"_":5},"gela","italy","sicily","siracusa","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","ancient greek",[],{"title":291,"body":292,"divs":293,"editions":318,"images":328,"handnote":344},"ISic001484. Epitaph of Philistidas, son of Euxenos","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-10-10\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\n                    Εὐξένο̄\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\">Φιλιστίδας\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐξένο̄\">Εὐξένο̄\u003C/span>\u003C/span> hο \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[κ]α̣λ̣ο̄ποιό&lt;ς&gt; \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-10-10\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\n                    Εὐξένο̄\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\">ΦΙΛΙΣΤΙΔΑΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐξένο̄\">ΕΥΞΕΝΟ̄\u003C/span>\u003C/span>HΟ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[.]..Ο̄ΠΟΙΟ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_copy2_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo V. Mignosa 2022-01-19\" src=\"ISic001484_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_copy2.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo V. Mignosa 2022-01-19\" src=\"ISic001484_copy2-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Trace of the cross bar of the Τ is visible\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Dubois: [κ]αλο̄ποιό(ς) \u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Philistidas, son of Euxenos, the ropemaker\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>An unusual example of an archaic funerary inscription with indication of the deceased's profession: the restoration of initial Κ and interpretation of καλωποιός as 'rope-maker' is due to Orsi. The stone was presumed lost by Dubois (and speculatively attributed to Palermo Museum in LSAG(2), but seems always to have been in the Syracuse museum since its deposit in 1900. \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1900 281-282 fig.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Hoffmann 1904 5216 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Roehl 1907 Tab.34 no.12 \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Jeffery 1961 278 no.54 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000677\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000677\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Dubois 1989 \u003Ca href=\"http://www.persee.fr/doc/efr_0000-0000_1989_cat_119_1\" target=\"_blank\">130\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Jeffery Johnston 1990 278 no.54 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000678\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000678\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Deeply cut letters of a regular, fairly square module, without serifs. Alpha with straight bar, standard delta, straight epsilon with equal bars, heta rectangular closed top and bottom, standard lambda, nu slants to the right, xsi in form of X, omicron of standard size, pi with shorter right hasta, four bar sigma with equal open strokes, phi with large eye and vetical stroke of equal size not over-extended.\u003C/p> Line 1  21-24  Line 2  20-22  Line 3  20-21  Interlineation line 1 to 2  10-13  Interlineation line 2 to 3  8  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[294,297,300,303,306,309,312,315],{"id":295,"html":296},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-10-10\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\n                    Εὐξένο̄\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\">Φιλιστίδας\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐξένο̄\">Εὐξένο̄\u003C/span>\u003C/span> hο \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[κ]α̣λ̣ο̄ποιό&lt;ς&gt; \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-10-10\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\n                    Εὐξένο̄\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\">ΦΙΛΙΣΤΙΔΑΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐξένο̄\">ΕΥΞΕΝΟ̄\u003C/span>\u003C/span>HΟ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[.]..Ο̄ΠΟΙΟ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":298,"html":299},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_copy2_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo V. Mignosa 2022-01-19\" src=\"ISic001484_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_copy2.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo V. Mignosa 2022-01-19\" src=\"ISic001484_copy2-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001484_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2016-10-10\" src=\"ISic001484_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":301,"html":302},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Trace of the cross bar of the Τ is visible\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"3\">3: \u003Cspan>Dubois: [κ]αλο̄ποιό(ς) \u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":304,"html":305},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Philistidas, son of Euxenos, the ropemaker\u003C/p>  ",{"id":307,"html":308},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>An unusual example of an archaic funerary inscription with indication of the deceased's profession: the restoration of initial Κ and interpretation of καλωποιός as 'rope-maker' is due to Orsi. The stone was presumed lost by Dubois (and speculatively attributed to Palermo Museum in LSAG(2), but seems always to have been in the Syracuse museum since its deposit in 1900. \u003C/p>  ",{"id":310,"html":311},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1900 281-282 fig.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Hoffmann 1904 5216 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Roehl 1907 Tab.34 no.12 \u003C/li>\u003Cli> Jeffery 1961 278 no.54 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000677\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000677\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Dubois 1989 \u003Ca href=\"http://www.persee.fr/doc/efr_0000-0000_1989_cat_119_1\" target=\"_blank\">130\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000187\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Jeffery Johnston 1990 278 no.54 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000678\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000678\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":313,"html":314},"handnote","\u003Cp>Deeply cut letters of a regular, fairly square module, without serifs. Alpha with straight bar, standard delta, straight epsilon with equal bars, heta rectangular closed top and bottom, standard lambda, nu slants to the right, xsi in form of X, omicron of standard size, pi with shorter right hasta, four bar sigma with equal open strokes, phi with large eye and vetical stroke of equal size not over-extended.\u003C/p> Line 1  21-24  Line 2  20-22  Line 3  20-21  Interlineation line 1 to 2  10-13  Interlineation line 2 to 3  8  ",{"id":316,"html":317},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[319,321,324,325],{"html":320},"Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa, Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2016-10-10",{"id":322,"lang":152,"html":323},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\n                    Εὐξένο̄\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\">Φιλιστίδας\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐξένο̄\">Εὐξένο̄\u003C/span>\u003C/span> hο \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[κ]α̣λ̣ο̄ποιό&lt;ς&gt; \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",{"html":320},{"id":326,"lang":152,"html":327},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\n                    Εὐξένο̄\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φιλιστίδας\">ΦΙΛΙΣΤΙΔΑΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Εὐξένο̄\">ΕΥΞΕΝΟ̄\u003C/span>\u003C/span>HΟ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[.]..Ο̄ΠΟΙΟ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>",[329,331,334,336,339,341],{"image":119,"thumb":330,"title":122},"ISic001484_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":332,"thumb":333,"title":122},"ISic001484.jpg","ISic001484-thumb.jpg",{"image":125,"thumb":335,"title":128},"ISic001484_copy2_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":337,"thumb":338,"title":128},"ISic001484_copy2.jpg","ISic001484_copy2-thumb.jpg",{"image":130,"thumb":340,"title":122},"ISic001484_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":342,"thumb":343,"title":122},"ISic001484_rear.jpg","ISic001484_rear-thumb.jpg",[345],{"html":55},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Epitaph of Philistidas, son of Euxenos\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JCu\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728\">James Cummings\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>conversion to EpiDoc\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n\t    \u003CrespStmt>\n     \t       \u003Cname xml:id=\"SS\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569\">Simona Stoyanova\u003C/name>\n     \t       \u003Cresp>standardisation of template and tidying up encoding\u003C/resp>\n \t   \u003C/respStmt>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"VM\" ref=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511\">Valentina Mignosa\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>encoding text division and checking the edition\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n            \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic001484\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\">644992\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001484\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"DOI\" when=\"2020-12-22\">10.5281/zenodo.4385958\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Siracusa\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097\">Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">19817\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>The upper part of a rectangular block of soft white/yellow limestone, intact top, right, left and to the rear, but broken unevenly across the lower edge. All the intact faces are squared off. Some chipping to the top front edge, and some loss to the face across the break on the lower edge. A pinkish vein runs across the upper part of the stone. The stone tapers very slightly in thickness towards the top.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.limestone\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html\">limestone\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.stele\" ref=\"https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/250\">stele\u003C/objectType>                                    \n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">10.8\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">23\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">7-7.5\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.damaged\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Three lines of Greek letters filling the width of the stone, and approximately justified left and right.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.deteriorated\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Deeply cut letters of a regular, fairly square module, without serifs. Alpha with straight bar, standard delta, straight epsilon with equal bars, heta rectangular closed top and bottom, standard lambda, nu slants to the right, xsi in form of X, omicron of standard size, pi with shorter right hasta, four bar sigma with equal open strokes, phi with large eye and vetical stroke of equal size not over-extended.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"21\" atMost=\"24\">21-24\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"20\" atMost=\"22\">20-22\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line3\" to=\"line3\">Line 3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"20\" atMost=\"21\">20-21\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"10\" atMost=\"13\">10-13\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line3\">Interlineation line 2 to 3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"8\" atMost=\"8\">8\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462214\">Gela\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2524653\">Gela\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.07381, 14.24038\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"-0525\" notAfter-custom=\"-0475\" evidence=\"lettering\">c. 500 BCE\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" when=\"1894\">Found on Capo Soprano, recovered c.1894 (according to the inventory) from the foundations of the villa of Conte Panebianco, and gifted to Siracusa museum by Pietro Rizza of Terranova\u003Cgeo>37.0741753,14.2292072\u003C/geo>. Now in Storeroom B, cassette 33.\u003C/provenance>\u003C!-- representative point on Capo Soprano -->\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" resp=\"#JP\" xml:id=\"autopsy\">Prag 2016-10-10\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n     